  "response_text": "An adult Black woman appears against a plain dark-to-gray studio background, facing forward as if addressing the viewer directly. She has short dark hair, small hoop earrings, and wears a bright red sweater with subtle horizontal stripes over a vivid pink collared shirt. Her expression is animated and emphatic: her eyes open wide, her eyebrows lift and tighten, and her mouth changes shape as she speaks. She turns her head slightly to one side with a skeptical look, then leans in again with widened eyes, creating a playful, exaggerated sense of surprise or disbelief.\n\nLarge white serif text then appears over her face like a multiple-choice quiz. The first visible line reads, “1. This woman is perfectly normal,” and then expands to, “This woman is perfectly normal. We’re the weirdos.” A second option appears below: “This woman can’t separate fact from fiction.” A third numbered option begins underneath, partially covering her face. She remains in the background, still staring forward with an intense, slightly comic expression while the quiz text dominates the screen.\n\nThe scene shifts to a product display: a bright orange-and-yellow box of “Tide with Bleach” stands upright against a dark studio background. The package has a radiant sunburst design, with the large blue-and-white “Tide” logo across the front and “with Bleach” below it. At the top of the box, small white text reads, “AVAILABLE IN LIMITED AREAS.” A bright white glow begins to shine from the center of the Tide logo, growing stronger until it washes over much of the box, turning the image into an almost solid burst of white light.\n\nAfter the flash, a single very dirty sock lies on a gray surface against a black background. The sock is yellowed and stained, with a ribbed cuff that has red, white, blue, and dark stripes. A cleaner, pale sock drops down and lands across it, forming an X shape, but the lower sock still looks heavily yellowed. At the bottom of the screen, small white text reads, “FOLLOW INSTRUCTIONS FOR TOUGH LAUNDRY.” Another sock then drops in from above and lands upright in front of the others. This front sock is much brighter white, with the same kind of colored striped cuff, making the contrast with the dirty yellow sock behind it clear.\n\nSeveral white socks then float and tumble through the dark studio space, as if tossed into the air. Some have colored striped cuffs, including red-and-white and blue-striped designs, and one smaller sock with yellow heel and toe areas spins away across the gray floor-like surface. The Tide with Bleach box reappears standing in the center, with socks flying around it and draping over it. Large white serif text across the lower part of the screen reads, “It’ll knock your socks off. And it’ll get ’em whiter.” Socks continue to fall and slide around the package: one white sock with blue stripes hangs over the top front edge of the box, others blur past on both sides, and more socks pile at the base. The final image holds on the bright Tide with Bleach box surrounded by scattered clean socks, with the slogan still visible at the bottom.",
